author: The Associated Press
title: Diverse Corona, Queens neighbourhood is featured in NYC 'Insider Guide'
text:
NEW YORK, N.Y. - New York City's official marketing and tourism group is showcasing the diverse Corona, Queens neighbourhood in its "Insider Guide."
NYC & Company said Wednesday that Corona is the "perfect neighbourhood to explore" for visitors who are in Queens for the U.S. Open tennis tournament.
The neighbourhood in north-central Queens includes Latin American, South Asian, Chinese and Korean immigrants. The No. 7 subway line is sometimes known as the "International Express."
In addition to dining and recreation, the attractions include the Queens Zoo, the New York Hall of Science and the Louis Armstrong House Museum.
NYC & Company unveiled the new guide Wednesday in India.
